Planocera graffi
was first described for the Gulf of Naples ( Lang 1879 , 1884 ), and also reported for the islands of Sao Vicente ( Cape Verde ) (
Laidlaw 1903
) and the Catalan coast (
Novell 2003
).

Planocera ceratommata

was originally described by 

Palombi (
1936
)

for Cape Town (
South Africa
), but more recently has been cited by 

Novell (
2003
)

for the Catalan coast.
